title: Access the CDC PLACES API
text: package allows users seamlessly query Centers Disease Control Prevention’s (CDC) Population Level Analysis Community Estimates (PLACES) API. CDC’s website: >PLACES collaboration CDC, Robert Wood Johnson Foundation, CDC Foundation. PLACES provides health data small areas across country. allows local health departments jurisdictions, regardless population size rurality, better understand burden geographic distribution health measures areas assist planning public health interventions. > >PLACES provides model-based, population-level analysis community estimates health measures counties, places (incorporated census designated places), census tracts, ZIP Code Tabulation Areas (ZCTAs) across United States. information data set’s methodology measure definitions refer CDC PLACES website.

text: get_places — function query PLACES API. Arguments allows user specify geography (census/county), state, measure, release (2020-2023), geometry (include shapefiles). get_dictionary — function pull full list measures available PLACES data set.

title: Obtain data from the CDC PLACES APIs. — get_places
code: get_places(   geography = "county",   state = NULL,   measure = NULL,   county = NULL,   release = "2023",   geometry = FALSE )

title: Obtain data from the CDC PLACES APIs. — get_places
text: geography level desired geography. Currently supports 'county', 'census', 'zcta'. state Specify state desired data using two letter abbreviation. Supports multiple states desired. measure Specify measures data pull. Supports multiple states desired. full list available measures, see function 'get_dictionary'. county Specify county desired data using full name county, capital letter. release Specify year release PLACES data set. Currently supports years 2020-2023. geometry FALSE (default), return regular data frame PLACES data. TRUE, uses tigris package return sf data frame simple feature geometry 'geometry' column.
